# HQ recurring jobs — executed by supercronic inside the hq container.
# 5-field cron syntax (m h dom mon dow); no user column.
# stdout/stderr are captured by supercronic and streamed to container logs.
#
# The container is the aster-side entry point of the queue architecture:
# it detects events (new mail / issue activity), files them as jobs under
# ~/HQ/queue, and runs lightweight single-message triage with a small local
# model. Heavy collect/full-sweep jobs are claimed by the Mac runner over ssh
# (scripts/hq-runner.sh) and processed on mtplx Qwen3.6-27B.

*/5  * * * * git -C /home/youruser/HQ pull --rebase --autostash origin main

*/5  * * * * /home/youruser/HQ/bin/hq queue scan
*/5  * * * * /home/youruser/HQ/bin/hq queue work --types triage,thread_update --max 3

# Mirror GitHub "Next" issues to Discord threads (open on Next, archive on
# close). 1 GraphQL call/run; reuses the hq-github Hermes bot token.
*/10 * * * * python3 /home/youruser/HQ/scripts/discord-issue-sync.py

# Dossier fallback: if the Mac runner falls behind (a collect job waits >20m)
# AND the GPUs are idle, aster processes collect jobs itself on local
# qwen3.6:27b. Holds (waits for next tick) whenever GPUs are busy.
*/10 * * * * /home/youruser/HQ/scripts/aster-collect-fallback.sh

# GTD daily/cleanup housekeeping (ported from GitHub Actions gtd-daily.yml /
# gtd-cleanup.yml). Container TZ is America/New_York, so these run at local
# 8am/2am — no more UTC/DST drift to reason about.
0 8 * * * /home/youruser/HQ/bin/hq task cron-daily
0 2 * * * /home/youruser/HQ/bin/hq task cron-cleanup
